{
  "texts": [
    "Time in the above figures is flowing from left to right as indicated.",
    "Since all four diagrams are equal for all g ∈ G (1), the 1-charges χ L 1 and χ L 2 of L 1 and L 2 respectively under G (1) 1-form symmetry must be equal.",
    "This equality can be interpreted as conservation of the 1-charge under time evolutions.",
    "characters of the 1-form symmetry group G (1).Mathematically, this is because there do not exist 1-morphisms between two simple objects in the 2-category formed by 2-representations of the 2-groupG (1) associated to a 1-form symmetry group G (1).",
    "Physically, this is the statement of charge conservation for 1-form symmetry as explained in figure 15."
  ]
}